  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "In de plots above, we can see that for a large angular distance, the fits don't line up with the first two datasets. The reason this happens is probably because of the high data density for lower distance, and improper choosing of the first estimate."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "print(myFit31.fit_report())\n",
    "print(myFit32.fit_report())\n",
    "print(myFit33.fit_report())"
